        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 29 at 4:40PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 440 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Roxboro, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Oxford, Roxboro, Stovall, Bushy Fork, Moriah, Berea, Surl, and Hyco
Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
